Police in Keiyo North have arrested an illicit alcohol distiller for assaulting his daughter after she refused to help him prepare chang’aa. The suspect beat up the secondary schoolgirl at his  home on Wednesday. Witnesses said the girl had refused to add ingredients to a drum of brew. Her furious father struck her with a plank of wood on the head. She was rushed to Iten County referral Hospital while angry villagers bayed for her father’s blood. "He was rescued by the chief. The villagers wanted to lynch him," a witness said. Keiyo North police boss Mwenda Meme said the man will be charged with assault. Click here for the latest political news